reviews.name: Elias H
reviews.text: This is the worst car rental company I have ever encountered and I traveled to many countries. These people are the real definition of scammers. Please stay away from this company and any of their affiliates. I rented a car from a company they work with called wheego in Rabat airport. Theyâ€™re in the parking lot and not inside the airport. When I tried to check out the car, they told me my credit card was declined for the deposit amount which was supposed to be â‚¬1400. They then told me that they will reduce to â‚¬950 euro for deposit amount but I will have to pay â‚¬60 fee. I knew that was a scam because my credit card was completely fine. I immediately called my credit card company and they told me that they didnâ€™t not even try to charge the â‚¬1400. When I told them this, they ask me to try the card again and charged â‚¬1500 and not the â‚¬1400 that was required. They just wanted to scam me for â‚¬60. And when I returned the car with zero damage, they tried to blame me for a tiny scratch less than 2 inches under the bumper. This is illegal in every other Countryâ€™s rental car companies to charge a customer for that tiny scratch on the bumper. They then blatantly lied to me and told to give them the card so that they can unblock the â‚¬1500. When  I gave  them my card, they returned the â‚¬1500 but charged another â‚¬1400 on my card. They then tried to call my insurance company and tried to make a claim on my behalf. The lady even told the insurance company that she was my sister. Luckily I have a video to prove that the scratch was already there. At the time I couldnâ€™t see the scratch on the video because it is so tiny. But when I got home, I rewatched the video and zoomed it. I couldnâ€™t believe it. Now I have notified the police, my insurance company and my credit card company. I made a dispute for that â‚¬1400 charge and now Iâ€™m going to court this Friday. These people are scammers, please stay away from them. This was the worst experience I have ever had. They are thieves and will look for anything to scam customers. Unbelievable!

reviews.text:
I participated in the 9 days long Atlas to Sahara tour. Viki was very kind and helpful in the preparation and answered every question I had. I arrived a few hours before the breefing from the airport with their transfer. We've got a thorough explanation of the tour by Greg. The handover in the first and last days went smooth. The guys are professional, friendly and very helpful, the only thing that did not cooperate through the week was the weather, but the guides adjusted the route based on the forecast.
I was a little bit slower, but I could catch up to the others and didn't get left behind. The food and accomodations were good. They can arrange vegetarian options if you want.
The days were diverse in riding time, distance and terrain with breathtaking scenery and enjoyable twisties on good tarmak.
Some advice if it's your first:
- If the description says you need warm stuff, you will need the warm stuff.
- Get enough cash, it's a must have at a lot of places.
- Get bottled water and sunscreen
- "Water is not freezing over 0, you can go faster"
All in all it was an amazing experience with unforgettable moments, friendly people and a lot of fun from the morning, through the day, til the evening. Best days of my year, I'd like to go back soon to another tour.

Days later I wanted to buy the helmet anyway, because my daughter came to visit me in  marroco and she needed a helmet.

They are selling used stuff and increase prices!

Uncool!

reviews.text:
Esperienza pessima â€“ sconsiglio vivamente!

Abbiamo noleggiato due Renault Clio Serie 5 quasi nuove: auto perfette, pulite e in ottime condizioni, con un prezzo tutto sommato competitivo. Purtroppo, tutto il resto Ã¨ stato estremamente deludente.

Durante la prenotazione ci era stato garantito che non sarebbe stata richiesta alcuna cauzione, ma al nostro arrivo a Marrakech ci hanno chiesto un deposito per entrambe le auto. Inizialmente sono stati irremovibili, affermando che loro lavorano sempre cosÃ¬, ignorando completamente quanto ci era stato detto in fase di prenotazione. Lâ€™attenzione al cliente? Zero.

Solo dopo una lunga discussione ci hanno consegnato i veicoli senza cauzione, ma il problema non Ã¨ finito lÃ¬. Al momento della restituzione si sono presentati in ritardo, mettendo a rischio la nostra partenza e creando ulteriore stress.

Il controllo finale delle auto Ã¨ stato a dir poco sospetto: si sono concentrati immediatamente su alcuni graffi che sembravano giÃ  conoscere perfettamente, dando lâ€™impressione che fossero giÃ  lÃ¬ da prima, o peggio, che li avessero provocati loro. Hanno preteso un pagamento extra per dei danni che non avevamo causato.

In conclusione: professionalitÃ  assente, comunicazione fuorviante, atteggiamento scorretto. Ãˆ stato il peggior autonoleggio con cui abbia mai avuto a che fare.
Sconsiglio caldamente di affidarsi a questa compagnia. Cambiare mestiere forse sarebbe la cosa migliore per loro

ENGLISH
Terrible experience â€“ strongly not recommended!

We rented two nearly-new Renault Clio Series 5 cars: the vehicles were flawless, clean, and in excellent condition, and the price was relatively competitive. Unfortunately, everything else about the experience was extremely disappointing.

During the booking process, we were clearly told that no security deposit would be required, but upon arrival in Marrakech, they asked us for a deposit for both vehicles. At first, they were completely inflexible, claiming that this was their usual policy, ignoring everything we had been told before. Customer service? Nonexistent.

After a long discussion, they finally handed over the cars without the deposit, but the problems didnâ€™t end there. When we returned the vehicles, they arrived late, nearly making us miss our return flight, adding more stress to an already frustrating experience.

The final inspection was highly suspicious: they immediately focused on specific scratches they seemed to know were there, giving us the impression they were either pre-existing or possibly even caused by them. They then demanded extra payment for damages we did not cause.

In summary: zero professionalism, misleading communication, and dishonest behavior. This was by far the worst car rental experience Iâ€™ve ever had.
I strongly advise against using this company. They should seriously consider a different line of work

reviews.name: Rafael
reviews.text: The best company i found. You pay all the first day (the car price and the insurance) and you are good to go. No km limits. Good car. Good price. I was scared to try because of the many scams you can find around. They proved to be trustworthy, clean and professional. They delivered the car in Marrakech. We needed to return it at the airport of Tangeri and they helped us by coming there (of course paying an extra, but who is so available?)! Also we had an old lady in bike coming against our car and scratching it (she was a scammer). They asked for 50â‚¬ for the damage and that's it (because the insurance is covering 90% and 10% you pay). Very easy going, not like the scams you hear that they ask for many many money. If someone goes to Morocco i recommend them!

reviews.text: I have hired van with driver twice with Red Platinum Tour now and both times my experience has been great. First time, I rented a 15 seater van and our drive was Br. Nour Din. We travelled a lot of places and he was with us the entire time for about 9 days. He was very well mannered, responsible and helpful. I would recommend him very highly. Second time, we just stayed for one day on transit and our driver was Br. Salim. He was very professional and knowledgeable about the places. First time, I went based on google reviews and was apprehensive as to what to expect. However, both times the car and the drivers were really good, on time, professional and friendly.  Dealing with Br. Hicham for tour arrangement was pleasant as well. I highly recommend this company for Morocco tour.

reviews.name: Sammy Ay
reviews.text:
Een van de jongens stond voor de deur van een bekende autoverhuurder en zei dat hij een betere prijs voor je zou regelen. Uiteindelijk was dat niet het geval. Er werd beloofd dat je een goede prijs zou krijgen, maar je werd toch een duurdere aanbieding gegeven. In de tussentijd had hij alles al geregeld. Bij het inleveren van de auto werden allerlei zaken opgenoemd om geld uit je krijgen. Hij heeft letterlijk 4 dingen opgenoemd die niet ter sprake waren.  De eigenaar zocht continu excuses om de borg in te houden. Uiteindelijk kreeg hij niets, maar hij heeft bijna een uur gezocht naar verschillende redenen om je toch te laten betalen.

Mijn advies: ga gewoon naar een betrouwbare verhuurder, waar je ook een all-risk verzekering kunt afsluiten en niet met dit soort situaties te maken hebt.

reviews.name: Ryan DCosta
reviews.text:
A big thanks to Aissam and Mehdi, for their invaluable support and like all Moroccon people they are most welcoming and warm.
Hands down the most trustworthy and best motorcycle rental agency in Marrakech.
We had rented 2 ktm 390s for a month to travel through Morocco and the Trans Morocco Trail.. The bikes given to us were impeccable and held up in all the extreme riding conditions..
Extremely Professional and supportive team from Aissam and Mehdi and the professional mechanics working on the Motorcyles.. the bikes were amazing and very in top notch condition to begin with..
They are crystal clear in their transactions and absolutely no hidden charges whatsoever. The deposit refund was done promptly even before we left the garage..
A big thanks to the Entire team of Tenere Riders..

reviews.name: ricsi fekete
reviews.text:
One of the worst car rental experiences Iâ€™ve ever had.
Iâ€™ve rented cars in many countries before and never had any issues, but this company was a total nightmare. They gave us a car with extremely worn-out, cracked tires. I drove carefully and only on main roads, but one tire completely failed, so I had to buy a new one myself for 1000 dirhams.
Later, a motorbike hit our car â€” the whole incident was clearly recorded on video showing it was not my fault at all. I sent them the video right away and asked for help, but they only responded the next day, saying Iâ€™d get no compensation unless I went to the police with a lawyer. This was shocking, especially since they had claimed to offer â€œthe best insurance.â€ The paint scratch was tiny and had already been there before the rental. Before I returned the car, they demanded 500 dirhams for the accident, I asked them if they will cover my 1000 dirhams expense for the tire they said they will if I can prove it's older than one year,and I had a proof in a photo. When we arrived an aggressive employee came, said the tire was only our responsibility, and asked now 1000 dirhams for the damage, and told us there is another damage on the car, but we had a proof when we picked up the car on the video that was there before our rental, but when we picked up the car it was night, but he said we caused this because he doesn't see.
He refused card payment, pocketed the cash, and gave no receipt. Iâ€™m convinced they never fixed the supposed damage and simply kept the money. When I asked for an invoice to file my travel insurance claim, I got no reply at all. After posting a review about this experience, their representative even called me asking to delete it and promised to â€œsettle things,â€ but of course, nothing ever happened.
During all these things I tried to be friendly and report anything.
Avoid this company entirely â€” dishonest, unprofessional, and completely unreliable.
